MARS MRT: H1 and Exploratory Analyses on Moderated Effect of Time

June 12, 2024

  • 1 H1 Main Analysis
    • 1.1 Estimated prevalence by group (marginal over time)
    • 1.2 Estimated effect on the log risk ratio scale
    • 1.3 Estimated effect on the risk ratio scale
    • 1.4 Estimated effect on the risk difference scale
  • 2 Exploratory Analysis (Linear Effect of Time)
    • 2.1 Day in study
    • 2.2 Hour of day
  • 3 Exploratory Analysis (Quadratic Effect of Time)
    • 3.1 Day in study
    • 3.2 Hour of day
  • 4 H1 Sensitivity Analysis
    • 4.1 Estimated prevalence by group
    • 4.2 Estimated effect on the log risk ratio scale
    • 4.3 Estimated effect on the risk difference scale

H1 Main Analysis excludes first and last days of the 10-day MRT while H1 Sensitivity Analysis includes all days of the 10-day MRT. In Exploratory Analysis on Moderated Effect of Time, we investigate whether the effect of prompt (versus no prompt) varies by day in study, where day in study is modeled in a linear or quadratic manner.
